The '''Acado virus''' (ACDV) is a serotype of [[Corriparta virus]] in the genus [[Orbivirus]] in the [[Corriparta serogroup]]. Isolated from [[Culex antennatus]] and [[C. univittatus neavi]] in [[Ethiopia]]. Not reported to cause disease in humans.<ref>{{cite book|last=Mahy|first=Brian W J|title=A dictionary of virology|date=2001|publisher=Academic Press|location=San Diego, Calif. [u.a.]|isbn=0-12-465327-8|pages=2|edition=3.}}</ref>

