{{multiple issues| {{COI|date=March 2013}} {{unreferenced|date=March 2013}} {{Orphan|date=February 2014}} }} {{Infobox book | name = Database System Concepts | title_orig = | translator = | image = Database System Concepts.jpg | caption = | author = [[Abraham Silberschatz]] and [[Hank Korth]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Computer Science]] | publisher = [[McGraw-Hill]] | pub_date = 1986 | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = 0-07-044752-7 }}
'''''Database System Concepts''''', by [[Abraham Silberschatz]] and [[Hank Korth]], is a classic{{Citation needed|date=March 2013}} textbook on [[database system|database systems]]. It is often called the sailboat book, because its first edition had on its cover a number of sailboats, labelled with the names of various [[database model|database models]]. The boats are sailing from a desert island towards a tropical island, while the wind pushes them away and prevents their arrival.
The book is currently in its sixth edition. The third edition added S. Sudrashan as an author.
