'''''Deinococcus murrayi''''' is a bacterium. It produces orange-pigmented colonies and has an optimum growth temperature of about {{convert|45|°C|°F}} to {{convert|50|°C|°F}}. It is extremely [[gamma radiation]]-resistant. Its type strain is ALT-1b (= DSM 11303).<ref name="FerreiraNobre1997">{{cite journal|last1=Ferreira|first1=A. C.|last2=Nobre|first2=M. F.|last3=Rainey|first3=F. A.|last4=Silva|first4=M. T.|last5=Wait|first5=R.|last6=Burghardt|first6=J.|last7=Chung|first7=A. P.|last8=Da Costa|first8=M. S.|title=Deinococcus geothermalis sp. nov. and Deinococcus murrayi sp. nov., Two Extremely Radiation-Resistant and Slightly Thermophilic Species from Hot Springs|journal=International Journal of Systematic Bacteriology|volume=47|issue=4|year=1997|pages=939–947|issn=0020-7713|doi=10.1099/00207713-47-4-939|pmid=9336890}}</ref>

